# GlassArc – Universal Local AI Assistant with Built‑In Web Search

**One file. Any GGUF model. Zero API keys.**  
GlassArc is a self‑contained, lightweight AI assistant that runs **any GGUF model** – from extreme 0.001‑bit quantizations up to full 16‑bit FP16 – directly on your CPU, while simultaneously performing live DuckDuckGo + Google web searches.  
No Gradio bloat, no venv restart loops, no format errors. Just download, run, and chat.

---

## ✨ Features

- **🤖 Local AI Chat** – Uses `llama-cpp-python` to load any GGUF model. Qwen2.5‑3B by default, but drop in your own.  
- **🌐 Live Web Search** – Scrapes DuckDuckGo + Google in parallel, with rotating user‑agents, polite delays, and **no API keys**.  
- **📚 Huge Context** – 8192 tokens (≈20 000 characters). Inputs exceeding the limit are automatically split, summarised, and merged – no “context overflow” errors.  
- **🔒 CRC Integrity** – CRC32 checksums (same as ZIP files) are stored alongside every text file for data verification.  
- **📝 Full Trace Logging** – Every operation (search, extraction, model call) is written to `glassarc_trace.log`. Operations >60s are logged to `slow_ops.log`.  
- **🖥️ Two Interfaces**  
  - **Terminal** – clean chat loop with `/web <query>` command.  
  - **Web UI** – lightweight Flask app that opens in your browser (no Gradio, no format issues).  
- **🧠 Universal Model Support** – Runs any GGUF file, regardless of quantization (IQ1_S, Q4_K_M, Q8_0, FP16, …) with **zero code changes**.  
- **🏋️ Lightweight** – The script itself is only ~30 KB. Resource usage is determined entirely by the model you choose.  
- **🔋 Privacy‑First** – 100% offline for AI; web search uses only public HTML pages. No telemetry, no data leaks.  

---

## 🪶 Lightweight, Yet Unlimited

| Model Precision | Typical RAM Usage | Works? |
|-----------------|-------------------|--------|
| IQ1_S (<1‑bit) | ~1 GB | ✅ |
| Q4_K_M (4‑bit) | ~2.5 GB | ✅ |
| Q8_0 (8‑bit) | ~4 GB | ✅ |
| FP16 (16‑bit) | ~7 GB | ✅ |
| Any other GGUF | Scales linearly | ✅ |

- **No code changes needed** – just place the GGUF in the `models/` folder and run the script.  
- **CPU only** – no GPU required, works on any laptop or desktop.  
- **Auto‑adaptation** – the model’s quantization metadata is read automatically, and the inference engine allocates exactly the resources needed.

